55// Helper to put several RTCP packets into lower layer datagram RTCP packet.
56class RTCPSender::PacketSender {
57 public:
58 PacketSender(rtcp::RtcpPacket::PacketReadyCallback callback,
59 size_t max_packet_size)
60 : callback_(callback), max_packet_size_(max_packet_size) {
61 RTC_CHECK_LE(max_packet_size, IP_PACKET_SIZE);
62 }
63 ~PacketSender() { RTC_DCHECK_EQ(index_, 0) << "Unsent rtcp packet."; }
64
65 // Appends a packet to pending compound packet.
66 // Sends rtcp packet if buffer is full and resets the buffer.
67 void AppendPacket(const rtcp::RtcpPacket& packet) {
68 packet.Create(buffer_, &index_, max_packet_size_, callback_);
69 }
70
71 // Sends pending rtcp packet.
72 void Send() {
73 if (index_ > 0) {
74 callback_(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t>(buffer_, index_));
75 index_ = 0;
76 }
77 }
78
79 private:
80 const rtcp::RtcpPacket::PacketReadyCallback callback_;
81 const size_t max_packet_size_;
82 size_t index_ = 0;
83 uint8_t buffer_[IP_PACKET_SIZE];
84};

118RTCPSender::RTCPSender(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config)
119 : audio_(config.audio),
120 ssrc_(config.local_media_ssrc),
121 clock_(config.clock),
122 random_(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()),
123 method_(RtcpMode::kOff),
124 event_log_(config.event_log),
125 transport_(config.outgoing_transport),
126 report_interval_ms_(config.rtcp_report_interval_ms > 0
127 ? config.rtcp_report_interval_ms
128 : (config.audio ? kDefaultAudioReportInterval
129 : kDefaultVideoReportInterval)),
130 sending_(false),
131 next_time_to_send_rtcp_(0),
132 timestamp_offset_(0),
133 last_rtp_timestamp_(0),
134 last_frame_capture_time_ms_(-1),
135 remote_ssrc_(0),
136 receive_statistics_(config.receive_statistics),
137
138 sequence_number_fir_(0),
139
140 remb_bitrate_(0),
141
142 tmmbr_send_bps_(0),
143 packet_oh_send_(0),
144 max_packet_size_(IP_PACKET_SIZE - 28), // IPv4 + UDP by default.
145
146 xr_send_receiver_reference_time_enabled_(
147 config.non_sender_rtt_measurement),
148 packet_type_counter_observer_(config.rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer),
149 send_video_bitrate_allocation_(false),
150 last_payload_type_(-1) {
151 RTC_DCHECK(transport_ != nullptr);
152
153 builders_[kRtcpSr] = &RTCPSender::BuildSR;
154 builders_[kRtcpRr] = &RTCPSender::BuildRR;
155 builders_[kRtcpSdes] = &RTCPSender::BuildSDES;
156 builders_[kRtcpPli] = &RTCPSender::BuildPLI;
157 builders_[kRtcpFir] = &RTCPSender::BuildFIR;
158 builders_[kRtcpRemb] = &RTCPSender::BuildREMB;
159 builders_[kRtcpBye] = &RTCPSender::BuildBYE;
160 builders_[kRtcpLossNotification] = &RTCPSender::BuildLossNotification;
161 builders_[kRtcpTmmbr] = &RTCPSender::BuildTMMBR;
162 builders_[kRtcpTmmbn] = &RTCPSender::BuildTMMBN;
163 builders_[kRtcpNack] = &RTCPSender::BuildNACK;
164 builders_[kRtcpAnyExtendedReports] = &RTCPSender::BuildExtendedReports;
165}

169RtcpMode RTCPSender::Status() const {
170 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
171 return method_;
172}
173
174void RTCPSender::SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode new_method) {
175 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
176
177 if (method_ == RtcpMode::kOff && new_method != RtcpMode::kOff) {
178 // When switching on, reschedule the next packet
179 next_time_to_send_rtcp_ =
180 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() + (report_interval_ms_ / 2);
181 }
182 method_ = new_method;
183}
184
185bool RTCPSender::Sending() const {
186 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
187 return sending_;
188}
189
190void RTCPSender::SetSendingStatus(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
191 bool sending) {
192 bool sendRTCPBye = false;
193 {
194 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
195
196 if (method_ != RtcpMode::kOff) {
197 if (sending == false && sending_ == true) {
198 // Trigger RTCP bye
199 sendRTCPBye = true;
200 }
201 }
202 sending_ = sending;
203 }
204 if (sendRTCPBye) {
205 if (SendRTCP(feedback_state, kRtcpBye) != 0) {
206 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to send RTCP BYE";
207 }
208 }
209}

211int32_t RTCPSender::SendLossNotification(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
212 uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
213 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
214 bool decodability_flag,
215 bool buffering_allowed) {
216 int32_t error_code = -1;
217 auto callback = [&](rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet) {
218 transport_->SendRtcp(packet.data(), packet.size());
219 error_code = 0;
220 if (event_log_) {
221 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRtcpPacketOutgoing>(packet));
222 }
223 };
224 absl::optional<PacketSender> sender;
225 {
226 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
227
228 if (!loss_notification_.Set(last_decoded_seq_num, last_received_seq_num,
229 decodability_flag)) {
230 return -1;
231 }
232
233 SetFlag(kRtcpLossNotification, /*is_volatile=*/true);
234
235 if (buffering_allowed) {
236 // The loss notification will be batched with additional feedback
237 // messages.
238 return 0;
239 }
240
241 sender.emplace(callback, max_packet_size_);
242 auto result = ComputeCompoundRTCPPacket(
243 feedback_state, RTCPPacketType::kRtcpLossNotification, 0, nullptr,
244 *sender);
245 if (result) {
246 return *result;
247 }
248 }
249 sender->Send();
250
251 return error_code;
252}

254void RTCPSender::SetRemb(int64_t bitrate_bps, std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs) {
255 RTC_CHECK_GE(bitrate_bps, 0);
256 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
257 remb_bitrate_ = bitrate_bps;
258 remb_ssrcs_ = std::move(ssrcs);
259
260 SetFlag(kRtcpRemb, /*is_volatile=*/false);
261 // Send a REMB immediately if we have a new REMB. The frequency of REMBs is
262 // throttled by the caller.
263 next_time_to_send_rtcp_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
264}
265
266void RTCPSender::UnsetRemb() {
267 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
268 // Stop sending REMB each report until it is reenabled and REMB data set.
269 ConsumeFlag(kRtcpRemb, /*forced=*/true);
270}

287void RTCPSender::SetLastRtpTime(uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
288 int64_t capture_time_ms,
289 int8_t payload_type) {
290 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
291 // For compatibility with clients who don't set payload type correctly on all
292 // calls.
293 if (payload_type != -1) {
294 last_payload_type_ = payload_type;
295 }
296 last_rtp_timestamp_ = rtp_timestamp;
297 if (capture_time_ms <= 0) {
298 // We don't currently get a capture time from VoiceEngine.
299 last_frame_capture_time_ms_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
300 } else {
301 last_frame_capture_time_ms_ = capture_time_ms;
302 }
303}

325bool RTCPSender::TimeToSendRTCPReport(bool sendKeyframeBeforeRTP) const {
326 /*
327 For audio we use a configurable interval (default: 5 seconds)
328
329 For video we use a configurable interval (default: 1 second) for a BW
330 smaller than 360 kbit/s, technicaly we break the max 5% RTCP BW for
331 video below 10 kbit/s but that should be extremely rare
332
333
334 From RFC 3550
335
336 MAX RTCP BW is 5% if the session BW
337 A send report is approximately 65 bytes inc CNAME
338 A receiver report is approximately 28 bytes
339
340 The RECOMMENDED value for the reduced minimum in seconds is 360
341 divided by the session bandwidth in kilobits/second. This minimum
342 is smaller than 5 seconds for bandwidths greater than 72 kb/s.
343
344 If the participant has not yet sent an RTCP packet (the variable
345 initial is true), the constant Tmin is set to half of the configured
346 interval.
347
348 The interval between RTCP packets is varied randomly over the
349 range [0.5,1.5] times the calculated interval to avoid unintended
350 synchronization of all participants
351
352 if we send
353 If the participant is a sender (we_sent true), the constant C is
354 set to the average RTCP packet size (avg_rtcp_size) divided by 25%
355 of the RTCP bandwidth (rtcp_bw), and the constant n is set to the
356 number of senders.
357
358 if we receive only
359 If we_sent is not true, the constant C is set
360 to the average RTCP packet size divided by 75% of the RTCP
361 bandwidth. The constant n is set to the number of receivers
362 (members - senders). If the number of senders is greater than
363 25%, senders and receivers are treated together.
364
365 reconsideration NOT required for peer-to-peer
366 "timer reconsideration" is
367 employed. This algorithm implements a simple back-off mechanism
368 which causes users to hold back RTCP packet transmission if the
369 group sizes are increasing.
370
371 n = number of members
372 C = avg_size/(rtcpBW/4)
373
374 3. The deterministic calculated interval Td is set to max(Tmin, n*C).
375
376 4. The calculated interval T is set to a number uniformly distributed
377 between 0.5 and 1.5 times the deterministic calculated interval.
378
379 5. The resulting value of T is divided by e-3/2=1.21828 to compensate
380 for the fact that the timer reconsideration algorithm converges to
381 a value of the RTCP bandwidth below the intended average
382 */
383
384 int64_t now = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
385
386 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
387
388 if (method_ == RtcpMode::kOff)
389 return false;
390
391 if (!audio_ && sendKeyframeBeforeRTP) {
392 // for video key-frames we want to send the RTCP before the large key-frame
393 // if we have a 100 ms margin
394 now += RTCP_SEND_BEFORE_KEY_FRAME_MS;
395 }
396
397 return now >= next_time_to_send_rtcp_;
398}

400void RTCPSender::BuildSR(const RtcpContext& ctx, PacketSender& sender) {
401 // Timestamp shouldn't be estimated before first media frame.
402 RTC_DCHECK_GE(last_frame_capture_time_ms_, 0);
403 // The timestamp of this RTCP packet should be estimated as the timestamp of
404 // the frame being captured at this moment. We are calculating that
405 // timestamp as the last frame's timestamp + the time since the last frame
406 // was captured.
407 int rtp_rate = rtp_clock_rates_khz_[last_payload_type_];
408 if (rtp_rate <= 0) {
409 rtp_rate =
410 (audio_ ? kBogusRtpRateForAudioRtcp : kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency) /
411 1000;
412 }
413 // Round now_us_ to the closest millisecond, because Ntp time is rounded
414 // when converted to milliseconds,
415 uint32_t rtp_timestamp =
416 timestamp_offset_ + last_rtp_timestamp_ +
417 ((ctx.now_us_ + 500) / 1000 - last_frame_capture_time_ms_) * rtp_rate;
418
419 rtcp::SenderReport report;
420 report.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
421 report.SetNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(ctx.now_us_));
422 report.SetRtpTimestamp(rtp_timestamp);
423 report.SetPacketCount(ctx.feedback_state_.packets_sent);
424 report.SetOctetCount(ctx.feedback_state_.media_bytes_sent);
425 report.SetReportBlocks(CreateReportBlocks(ctx.feedback_state_));
426 sender.AppendPacket(report);
427}

478void RTCPSender::BuildTMMBR(const RtcpContext& ctx, PacketSender& sender) {
479 if (ctx.feedback_state_.receiver == nullptr)
480 return;
481 // Before sending the TMMBR check the received TMMBN, only an owner is
482 // allowed to raise the bitrate:
483 // * If the sender is an owner of the TMMBN -> send TMMBR
484 // * If not an owner but the TMMBR would enter the TMMBN -> send TMMBR
485
486 // get current bounding set from RTCP receiver
487 bool tmmbr_owner = false;
488
489 // holding mutex_rtcp_sender_ while calling RTCPreceiver which
490 // will accuire criticalSectionRTCPReceiver_ is a potental deadlock but
491 // since RTCPreceiver is not doing the reverse we should be fine
492 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> candidates =
493 ctx.feedback_state_.receiver->BoundingSet(&tmmbr_owner);
494
495 if (!candidates.empty()) {
496 for (const auto& candidate : candidates) {
497 if (candidate.bitrate_bps() == tmmbr_send_bps_ &&
498 candidate.packet_overhead() == packet_oh_send_) {
499 // Do not send the same tuple.
500 return;
501 }
502 }
503 if (!tmmbr_owner) {
504 // Use received bounding set as candidate set.
505 // Add current tuple.
506 candidates.emplace_back(ssrc_, tmmbr_send_bps_, packet_oh_send_);
507
508 // Find bounding set.
509 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> bounding =
510 TMMBRHelp::FindBoundingSet(std::move(candidates));
511 tmmbr_owner = TMMBRHelp::IsOwner(bounding, ssrc_);
512 if (!tmmbr_owner) {
513 // Did not enter bounding set, no meaning to send this request.
514 return;
515 }
516 }
517 }
518
519 if (!tmmbr_send_bps_)
520 return;
521
522 rtcp::Tmmbr tmmbr;
523 tmmbr.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
524 rtcp::TmmbItem request;
525 request.set_ssrc(remote_ssrc_);
526 request.set_bitrate_bps(tmmbr_send_bps_);
527 request.set_packet_overhead(packet_oh_send_);
528 tmmbr.AddTmmbr(request);
529 sender.AppendPacket(tmmbr);
530}
531
532void RTCPSender::BuildTMMBN(const RtcpContext& ctx, PacketSender& sender) {
533 rtcp::Tmmbn tmmbn;
534 tmmbn.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
535 for (const rtcp::TmmbItem& tmmbr : tmmbn_to_send_) {
536 if (tmmbr.bitrate_bps() > 0) {
537 tmmbn.AddTmmbr(tmmbr);
538 }
539 }
540 sender.AppendPacket(tmmbn);
541}

556void RTCPSender::BuildNACK(const RtcpContext& ctx, PacketSender& sender) {
557 rtcp::Nack nack;
558 nack.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
559 nack.SetMediaSsrc(remote_ssrc_);
560 nack.SetPacketIds(ctx.nack_list_, ctx.nack_size_);
561
562 // Report stats.
563 for (int idx = 0; idx < ctx.nack_size_; ++idx) {
564 nack_stats_.ReportRequest(ctx.nack_list_[idx]);
565 }
566 packet_type_counter_.nack_requests = nack_stats_.requests();
567 packet_type_counter_.unique_nack_requests = nack_stats_.unique_requests();
568
569 ++packet_type_counter_.nack_packets;
570 sender.AppendPacket(nack);
571}

573void RTCPSender::BuildBYE(const RtcpContext& ctx, PacketSender& sender) {
574 rtcp::Bye bye;
575 bye.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
576 bye.SetCsrcs(csrcs_);
577 sender.AppendPacket(bye);
578}
579
580void RTCPSender::BuildExtendedReports(const RtcpContext& ctx,
581 PacketSender& sender) {
582 rtcp::ExtendedReports xr;
583 xr.SetSenderSsrc(ssrc_);
584
585 if (!sending_ && xr_send_receiver_reference_time_enabled_) {
586 rtcp::Rrtr rrtr;
587 rrtr.SetNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(ctx.now_us_));
588 xr.SetRrtr(rrtr);
589 }
590
591 for (const rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo& rti : ctx.feedback_state_.last_xr_rtis) {
592 xr.AddDlrrItem(rti);
593 }
594
595 if (send_video_bitrate_allocation_) {
596 rtcp::TargetBitrate target_bitrate;
597
598 for (int sl = 0; sl < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++sl) {
599 for (int tl = 0; tl < kMaxTemporalStreams; ++tl) {
600 if (video_bitrate_allocation_.HasBitrate(sl, tl)) {
601 target_bitrate.AddTargetBitrate(
602 sl, tl, video_bitrate_allocation_.GetBitrate(sl, tl) / 1000);
603 }
604 }
605 }
606
607 xr.SetTargetBitrate(target_bitrate);
608 send_video_bitrate_allocation_ = false;
609 }
610 sender.AppendPacket(xr);
611}
612
613int32_t RTCPSender::SendRTCP(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
614 RTCPPacketType packet_type,
615 int32_t nack_size,
616 const uint16_t* nack_list) {
617 int32_t error_code = -1;
618 auto callback = [&](rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet) {
619 if (transport_->SendRtcp(packet.data(), packet.size())) {
620 error_code = 0;
621 if (event_log_) {
622 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRtcpPacketOutgoing>(packet));
623 }
624 }
625 };
626 absl::optional<PacketSender> sender;
627 {
628 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
629 sender.emplace(callback, max_packet_size_);
630 auto result = ComputeCompoundRTCPPacket(feedback_state, packet_type,
631 nack_size, nack_list, *sender);
632 if (result) {
633 return *result;
634 }
635 }
636 sender->Send();
637
638 return error_code;
639}
640
641absl::optional<int32_t> RTCPSender::ComputeCompoundRTCPPacket(
642 const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
643 RTCPPacketType packet_type,
644 int32_t nack_size,
645 const uint16_t* nack_list,
646 PacketSender& sender) {
647 if (method_ == RtcpMode::kOff) {
648 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Can't send rtcp if it is disabled.";
649 return -1;
650 }
651 // Add the flag as volatile. Non volatile entries will not be overwritten.
652 // The new volatile flag will be consumed by the end of this call.
653 SetFlag(packet_type, true);
654
655 // Prevent sending streams to send SR before any media has been sent.
656 const bool can_calculate_rtp_timestamp = (last_frame_capture_time_ms_ >= 0);
657 if (!can_calculate_rtp_timestamp) {
658 bool consumed_sr_flag = ConsumeFlag(kRtcpSr);
659 bool consumed_report_flag = sending_ && ConsumeFlag(kRtcpReport);
660 bool sender_report = consumed_report_flag || consumed_sr_flag;
661 if (sender_report && AllVolatileFlagsConsumed()) {
662 // This call was for Sender Report and nothing else.
663 return 0;
664 }
665 if (sending_ && method_ == RtcpMode::kCompound) {
666 // Not allowed to send any RTCP packet without sender report.
667 return -1;
668 }
669 }
670
671 if (packet_type_counter_.first_packet_time_ms == -1)
672 packet_type_counter_.first_packet_time_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
673
674 // We need to send our NTP even if we haven't received any reports.
675 RtcpContext context(feedback_state, nack_size, nack_list,
676 clock_->TimeInMicroseconds());
677
678 PrepareReport(feedback_state);
679
680 bool create_bye = false;
681
682 auto it = report_flags_.begin();
683 while (it != report_flags_.end()) {
684 uint32_t rtcp_packet_type = it->type;
685
686 if (it->is_volatile) {
687 report_flags_.erase(it++);
688 } else {
689 ++it;
690 }
691
692 // If there is a BYE, don't append now - save it and append it
693 // at the end later.
694 if (rtcp_packet_type == kRtcpBye) {
695 create_bye = true;
696 continue;
697 }
698 auto builder_it = builders_.find(rtcp_packet_type);
699 if (builder_it == builders_.end()) {
700 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Could not find builder for packet type "
701 << rtcp_packet_type;
702 } else {
703 BuilderFunc func = builder_it->second;
704 (this->*func)(context, sender);
705 }
706 }
707
708 // Append the BYE now at the end
709 if (create_bye) {
710 BuildBYE(context, sender);
711 }
712
713 if (packet_type_counter_observer_ != nullptr) {
714 packet_type_counter_observer_->RtcpPacketTypesCounterUpdated(
715 remote_ssrc_, packet_type_counter_);
716 }
717
718 RTC_DCHECK(AllVolatileFlagsConsumed());
719 return absl::nullopt;
720}
721
722void RTCPSender::PrepareReport(const FeedbackState& feedback_state) {
723 bool generate_report;
724 if (IsFlagPresent(kRtcpSr) || IsFlagPresent(kRtcpRr)) {
725 // Report type already explicitly set, don't automatically populate.
726 generate_report = true;
727 RTC_DCHECK(ConsumeFlag(kRtcpReport) == false);
728 } else {
729 generate_report =
730 (ConsumeFlag(kRtcpReport) && method_ == RtcpMode::kReducedSize) ||
731 method_ == RtcpMode::kCompound;
732 if (generate_report)
733 SetFlag(sending_ ? kRtcpSr : kRtcpRr, true);
734 }
735
736 if (IsFlagPresent(kRtcpSr) || (IsFlagPresent(kRtcpRr) && !cname_.empty()))
737 SetFlag(kRtcpSdes, true);
738
739 if (generate_report) {
740 if ((!sending_ && xr_send_receiver_reference_time_enabled_) ||
741 !feedback_state.last_xr_rtis.empty() ||
742 send_video_bitrate_allocation_) {
743 SetFlag(kRtcpAnyExtendedReports, true);
744 }
745
746 // generate next time to send an RTCP report
747 int min_interval_ms = report_interval_ms_;
748
749 if (!audio_ && sending_) {
750 // Calculate bandwidth for video; 360 / send bandwidth in kbit/s.
751 int send_bitrate_kbit = feedback_state.send_bitrate / 1000;
752 if (send_bitrate_kbit != 0) {
753 min_interval_ms = 360000 / send_bitrate_kbit;
754 min_interval_ms = std::min(min_interval_ms, report_interval_ms_);
755 }
756 }
757
758 // The interval between RTCP packets is varied randomly over the
759 // range [1/2,3/2] times the calculated interval.
760 int time_to_next =
761 random_.Rand(min_interval_ms * 1 / 2, min_interval_ms * 3 / 2);
762
763 RTC_DCHECK_GT(time_to_next, 0);
764 next_time_to_send_rtcp_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() + time_to_next;
765
766 // RtcpSender expected to be used for sending either just sender reports
767 // or just receiver reports.
768 RTC_DCHECK(!(IsFlagPresent(kRtcpSr) && IsFlagPresent(kRtcpRr)));
769 }
770}
771
772std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock> RTCPSender::CreateReportBlocks(
773 const FeedbackState& feedback_state) {
774 std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock> result;
775 if (!receive_statistics_)
776 return result;
777
778 // TODO(danilchap): Support sending more than |RTCP_MAX_REPORT_BLOCKS| per
779 // compound rtcp packet when single rtcp module is used for multiple media
780 // streams.
781 result = receive_statistics_->RtcpReportBlocks(RTCP_MAX_REPORT_BLOCKS);
782
783 if (!result.empty() && ((feedback_state.last_rr_ntp_secs != 0) ||
784 (feedback_state.last_rr_ntp_frac != 0))) {
785 // Get our NTP as late as possible to avoid a race.
786 uint32_t now = CompactNtp(TimeMicrosToNtp(clock_->TimeInMicroseconds()));
787
788 uint32_t receive_time = feedback_state.last_rr_ntp_secs & 0x0000FFFF;
789 receive_time <<= 16;
790 receive_time += (feedback_state.last_rr_ntp_frac & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
791
792 uint32_t delay_since_last_sr = now - receive_time;
793 // TODO(danilchap): Instead of setting same value on all report blocks,
794 // set only when media_ssrc match sender ssrc of the sender report
795 // remote times were taken from.
796 for (auto& report_block : result) {
797 report_block.SetLastSr(feedback_state.remote_sr);
798 report_block.SetDelayLastSr(delay_since_last_sr);
799 }
800 }
801 return result;
802}

807 csrcs_ = csrcs;

815
816void RTCPSender::SetFlag(uint32_t type, bool is_volatile) {
817 if (type & kRtcpAnyExtendedReports) {
818 report_flags_.insert(ReportFlag(kRtcpAnyExtendedReports, is_volatile));
819 } else {
820 report_flags_.insert(ReportFlag(type, is_volatile));
821 }
822}
823
824bool RTCPSender::IsFlagPresent(uint32_t type) const {
825 return report_flags_.find(ReportFlag(type, false)) != report_flags_.end();
826}
827
828bool RTCPSender::ConsumeFlag(uint32_t type, bool forced) {
829 auto it = report_flags_.find(ReportFlag(type, false));
830 if (it == report_flags_.end())
831 return false;
832 if (it->is_volatile || forced)
833 report_flags_.erase((it));
834 return true;
835}
836
837bool RTCPSender::AllVolatileFlagsConsumed() const {
838 for (const ReportFlag& flag : report_flags_) {
839 if (flag.is_volatile)
840 return false;
841 }
842 return true;
843}
844
845void RTCPSender::SetVideoBitrateAllocation(
846 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate) {
847 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
848 // Check if this allocation is first ever, or has a different set of
849 // spatial/temporal layers signaled and enabled, if so trigger an rtcp report
850 // as soon as possible.
851 absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation> new_bitrate =
852 CheckAndUpdateLayerStructure(bitrate);
853 if (new_bitrate) {
854 video_bitrate_allocation_ = *new_bitrate;
855 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Emitting TargetBitrate XR for SSRC " << ssrc_
856 << " with new layers enabled/disabled: "
857 << video_bitrate_allocation_.ToString();
858 next_time_to_send_rtcp_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
859 } else {
860 video_bitrate_allocation_ = bitrate;
861 }
862
863 send_video_bitrate_allocation_ = true;
864 SetFlag(kRtcpAnyExtendedReports, true);
865}
866
867absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation> RTCPSender::CheckAndUpdateLayerStructure(
868 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate) const {
869 absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation> updated_bitrate;
870 for (size_t si = 0; si < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++si) {
871 for (size_t ti = 0; ti < kMaxTemporalStreams; ++ti) {
872 if (!updated_bitrate &&
873 (bitrate.HasBitrate(si, ti) !=
874 video_bitrate_allocation_.HasBitrate(si, ti) ||
875 (bitrate.GetBitrate(si, ti) == 0) !=
876 (video_bitrate_allocation_.GetBitrate(si, ti) == 0))) {
877 updated_bitrate = bitrate;
878 }
879 if (video_bitrate_allocation_.GetBitrate(si, ti) > 0 &&
880 bitrate.GetBitrate(si, ti) == 0) {
881 // Make sure this stream disabling is explicitly signaled.
882 updated_bitrate->SetBitrate(si, ti, 0);
883 }
884 }
885 }
886
887 return updated_bitrate;
888}
889
890void RTCPSender::SendCombinedRtcpPacket(
891 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> rtcp_packets) {
892 size_t max_packet_size;
893 uint32_t ssrc;
894 {
895 MutexLock lock(&mutex_rtcp_sender_);
896 if (method_ == RtcpMode::kOff) {
897 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Can't send rtcp if it is disabled.";
898 return;
899 }
900
901 max_packet_size = max_packet_size_;
902 ssrc = ssrc_;
903 }
904 RTC_DCHECK_LE(max_packet_size, IP_PACKET_SIZE);
905 auto callback = [&](rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet) {
906 if (transport_->SendRtcp(packet.data(), packet.size())) {
907 if (event_log_)
908 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRtcpPacketOutgoing>(packet));
909 }
910 };
911 PacketSender sender(callback, max_packet_size);
912 for (auto& rtcp_packet : rtcp_packets) {
913 rtcp_packet->SetSenderSsrc(ssrc);
914 sender.AppendPacket(*rtcp_packet);
915 }
916 sender.Send();
917}
